text:
Jimmy Garoppolo is the 49ers' most talked about player, but he hasn’t been talking to reporters this offseason. He broke a sixth-month silence when he spoke, via Zoom, with a group of local reporters for the first time since Feb. 5.

name: sfchronicle
text:
Many Bay Area parkgoers, when interviewed about their mask choices, said they feel safe without a face covering when sitting outside with friends they trust. 

When do you choose to wear a mask, and when do you feel safe? 

Let us know: https://t.co/IzzZti04oV

text: Santa Clara County health officials reported 240 new coronavirus cases, bringing the case total to 11,030. Officials also reported one more COVID-19 death, bringing the county’s death total to 192, according to the county's COVID-19 data dashboard. https://t.co/7MO3i4KBDP

text:

text: “I used to get tormented a little bit,” Toney said. “Black kids in my neighborhood would say, ‘What are you doing? We don’t play golf.’ And white kids at the course would say, ‘You don’t belong out here.’ All that did was motivate me more.” https://t.co/LuIFhfomM5
